wikipedia_page.main: Frederick Octavius Pickard-Cambridge (3 November 1860 – 9 February 1905) was an English arachnologist. He is sometimes confused  with his uncle, Octavius Pickard-Cambridge (1828–1917), who was also an arachnologist and from whom  F. O. Pickard-Cambridge picked up his enthusiasm for the study of spiders.
